<subSubSection id="C30F0386B13FFF9DFF55F9E5FB57F886" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="124" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13FFF9AFF55F9E5FE59F961" blockId="10.[166,1225,1535,1850]" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
D i a g n o s i s. This species is distinguished from all other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13FFF9AFB8EF9E5FBF1F9A1" authorityName="Coquillett" authorityYear="1898" box="[1024,1143,1536,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFB8EF9E5FBF1F9A1" box="[1024,1143,1536,1561]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">Eupyrgota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of its large size, bicoloured brown-yellow body and wing, well-developed facial carina, parafacial shining, narrow, half as wide as eye horizontal diameter, eye vertical diameter more than 3 times (3.7×) as high as gena, moderately narrow legs and petiolate abdomen, slightly wrinkled fronto-orbital plate and parafacial, 3 pairs of scutellar setae, and presence of small femoral organ in female. See the key in the remarks below for differences from related species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13FFF9DFF55F905FCF5FE12" blockId="10.[166,1225,1535,1850]" lastBlockId="13.[174,1233,175,1482]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="124" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Head (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13FFF9AFE7FF93AFDA8F941" box="[497,558,1759,1785]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[166,199,1666,1688]" captionTargetBox="[220,1195,215,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-8@12.[188,1210,206,1590]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., holotype ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–5 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — anterior; 4 — left; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior; 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, ventral. Рис. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., голотип ♀ (NMKE): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2–5 — голова (2 — спереди слева;3 — спереди; 4 — слева;5 — дорсально); 6 — переднее бедро,вид сзади;7 — среднее бедро, спереди; 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко, вентрально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403943/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">fig. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B13FFF9AFDB4F93AFDE3F941" box="[570,613,1759,1785]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStart-3="Fig" captionStartId-0="6.[166,199,1357,1379]" captionStartId-1="7.[176,209,1342,1364]" captionStartId-2="9.[174,207,1641,1663]" captionStartId-3="11.[174,207,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox-0="[196,1203,181,1342]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1203,178,1317]" captionTargetBox-2="[263,1145,180,1601]" captionTargetBox-3="[226,1185,174,1660]" captionTargetId-0="figure-176@6.[196,1203,174,1356]" captionTargetId-1="figure-181@7.[194,1204,174,1318]" captionTargetId-2="figure-5@9.[191,1208,174,1626]" captionTargetId-3="figure-5@11.[226,1188,174,1676]" captionTargetPageId-0="6" captionTargetPageId-1="7" captionTargetPageId-2="9" captionTargetPageId-3="11" captionText-0="Fig.2. Eupyrgota alienata, holotype ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) and non-type ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — habitus, dorsal; 2 — labels; 3–4 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior); 5 — wing; 6 — fore coxa. Рис. 2. Eupyrgota alienata, голотип ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) и нетиповая ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — общий вид, дорсально; 2 — этикетки; 3–4 — голова (3 — слева; 4 — спереди); 5 — крыло; 6 — передний тазик." captionText-1="Fig. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — wing; 7 — mid femur and tibia, anterior; 8 — abdomen, left. Рис. 3. Eupyrgota angustifrons, голотип ♀ (BMNH): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2 — этикетки; 3–5 — голова (3 — слева;4 — спереди;5 — дорсально); 6 — крыло; 7 — среднее бедро и голень, спереди;8 — брюшко,слева." captionText-2="Fig. 4. Eupyrgota armipes, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 1 — habitus, left; 2 — labels; 3–5 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur and tibia, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior view; 8 — fore trochanter; 9 — mid trochanter; 10 — wing; 11 — mesonotum and abdomen, dorsally; 12 — abdomen, posterior." captionText-3="Fig. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, holotype ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) and holotype ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — habitus, dorsal; 5 — same, left; 2, 4 — labels; 6–7 — head (3 — anterior left view; 4 — dorsal); 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, dorsally. Рис. 5. Eupyrgota brahma, голотип ♀ Adapsilia brahma (BMNH) (1–2) и голотип ♀ Adapsilia nocturna (BMNH) (3–9): 1, 3 — общий вид, дорсально; 5 — same, слева; 2, 4 — этикетки; 6–7 — голова (3 — спереди слева view; 4 — дорсально); 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко,дорсально." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403935" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403937" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403939" figureDoi-3="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403941" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6403935/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6403937/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6403939/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/6403941/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13FFF9AFDB4F93AFDE3F941" box="[570,613,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="121">2–5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
) brown, with partly yellow vertex, face and occiput; frons 1.35× (at vertex) and 1.7× as wide as eye (at lunule level), conspicuously broadened anteriorly; eye oval (eye ratio 0.55); genal-eye ratio 0.27; antenna dark brown to black; first flagellomere-pedicel ratio 1.25; medial vertical seta 0.2× as long as vertical diameter of eye; lateral vertical seta non-distinguishable from postocular setulae; postocellar, three ocellar and orbital setae 0.6–0.8× as long as medial vertical seta. Fronto-orbital plates and parafacial shining, yellowish brown to dark brown, with sparse shallow wrinkles and pits (
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B138FF9DFF38FECAFE89FEF1" box="[182,271,303,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[166,199,1357,1379]" captionTargetBox="[196,1203,181,1342]" captionTargetId="figure-176@6.[196,1203,174,1356]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig.2. Eupyrgota alienata, holotype ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) and non-type ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — habitus, dorsal; 2 — labels; 3–4 — head (3 — left; 4 — anterior); 5 — wing; 6 — fore coxa. Рис. 2. Eupyrgota alienata, голотип ♀ (BMNH) (1–2) и нетиповая ♀ (NHMB) (3–6): 1 — общий вид, дорсально; 2 — этикетки; 3–4 — голова (3 — слева; 4 — спереди); 5 — крыло; 6 — передний тазик." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403935/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="124">
fig. 2, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB138FF9DFE8FFECAFE89FEF1" box="[257,271,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="124">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Antennal groove brownish yellow, with dark brown ventral margin. Gena dark brown. Epistoma black, 0.17× as high as facial carina. Supracervical area with dark brown spot. Palp as long as flagellomere 1; 3× as long as wide, black at base, dark yellow, moderately short black setulose and gray microtrichose on the rest.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6A0085B13EFF9BFF20F975FD29F884" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403941" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6403941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403941/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="122" startId="11.[174,207,1680,1702]" targetBox="[226,1185,174,1660]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB13EFF9BFF20F975FDC2F963" blockId="11.[174,1232,1680,1756]" pageId="11" pageNumber="122">
Fig. 5. 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13EFF9BFF7CF974FE2BF91D" box="[242,429,1680,1702]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="122">
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13EFF9BFF7CF974FE2FF91D" authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[242,425,1680,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brahma">Eupyrgota brahma</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
holotype ♀ 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB13EFF9BFDA9F975FCB3F91E" authority="(BMNH)" baseAuthorityName="BMNH" box="[551,821,1680,1702]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Adapsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brahma">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB13EFF9BFDA9F975FD53F91D" box="[551,725,1680,1701]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="122">Adapsilia brahma</emphasis>
(BMNH)
</taxonomicName>
(
